resources.string:
Din app för att mäta internetcensur.

Är webbsidor och sociala medier appar blockerade? Är din internetanslutning ovanligt långsam?

Kör OONI Probe för att få reda på det!
OONI data publiceras öppet och kommer att innehålla din nätverksinformation.
Någon som övervakar din internetanvändning (t.ex myndighet eller Internetleverantör) kommer se att du kör OONI Probe.
Du kommer eventuellt att testa förbjudna webbsidor (men du kan välja vilka sidor du vill testa).
Om någon bevakar din internetanvändning, kommer de att se att du kör OONI Probe.
OONI Probe är inte ett integritetsverktyg. Om någon bevakar din internetanvändning kommer de se vilken mjukvara du kör.
Varje gång jag kör OONI Probe, kommer nätverksinformation jag samlar att automatiskt publiceras.
För att öka transparensen av internetcensur, kommer nätverksinformation från samtliga OONI Probe användare att automatiskt publiceras (om de inte stänger av det i inställningar).
To improve OONI Probe we would like to collect anonymous crash reports when the app does not work properly.\n\nWould you like yo opt-in to submitting crash reports to the OONI development team?
Vi gör vårt bästa för att inte publicera din IP-adress eller annan potentiellt personlig information\n\nLär dig mer genom [OONI\'s Data Policy](https://ooni.io/about/data-policy/).
By tapping \"OK\", you will share crash reports to help us improve OONI Probe.
Finishing the currently pending tests, please wait...

Kontrollera om webbsidor är blockerade med hjälp av OONI's [Web Connectivity test](https://ooni.io/nettest/web-connectivity/).

Varje gång du trycker på kör, så testar du olika webbsidor från Citizen Lab's [global](https://github.com/citizenlab/test-lists/blob/master/lists/global.csv) och [country-specific](https://github.com/citizenlab/test-lists/tree/master/lists) testlistor.

För att testa utvalda sidor, tryck på Välj Webbsidor-knappen eller välj kategorier av sidor genom inställningarna.

Det här testat kontrollerar om webbsidor är blockerade genom att använda DNS tampering, TCP/IP blocking eller genom en transparent HTTP proxy

Dina resultat kommer att publiceras på [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.io/world/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

Check whether websites are blocked using OONI's [Web Connectivity test](https://ooni.io/nettest/web-connectivity/).

You will test the websites included in the Citizen Lab's [global](https://github.com/citizenlab/test-lists/blob/master/lists/global.csv) and [country-specific](https://github.com/citizenlab/test-lists/tree/master/lists) test lists.

This test measures whether websites are blocked by means of DNS tampering, TCP/IP blocking or by a transparent HTTP proxy.

Your results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.org/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

Measure the speed and performance of your network using the [NDT](https://ooni.io/nettest/ndt/) test.

Measure video streaming performance using the [DASH](https://ooni.io/nettest/dash/) test.

These tests consume data depending on your network speed.

Your results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.io/world/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

Disclaimer: These tests rely on third party servers. We therefore cannot guarantee that your IP address will not be collected.

By running the tests in this card, you will:

- Measure the speed and performance of your network ([NDT](https://ooni.org/nettest/ndt/) test)
- Measure video streaming performance ([DASH](https://ooni.org/nettest/dash/) test)
- Check for the presence of [middlebox technologies](https://ooni.org/support/glossary/#middlebox) on your network ([HTTP Invalid Request Line](https://ooni.org/nettest/http-invalid-request-line/) and [HTTP Header Field Manipulation](https://ooni.org/nettest/http-header-field-manipulation/) tests)

These tests consume data depending on your network speed.

Your test results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.org/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

**Disclaimer:** The [NDT](https://ooni.org/nettest/ndt/) and [DASH](https://ooni.org/nettest/dash/) tests are conducted against third-party servers provided by [Measurement Lab (M-Lab)](https://www.measurementlab.net/). If you run these tests, M-Lab will collect and publish your IP address (for research purposes), irrespective of your OONI Probe settings. Learn more about M-Lab’s data governance through its [privacy statement](https://www.measurementlab.net/privacy/).

Internet Service Providers often use network appliances (middleboxes) for various networking purposes (such as caching). Sometimes these middleboxes are used to implement internet censorship and/or surveillance.

Find middleboxes in your network using OONI's [HTTP Invalid Request Line](https://ooni.io/nettest/http-invalid-request-line/) and [HTTP Header Field Manipulation](https://ooni.io/nettest/http-header-field-manipulation/) tests.

Your results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.io/world/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

Check whether [WhatsApp](https://ooni.org/nettest/whatsapp/), [Facebook Messenger](https://ooni.org/nettest/facebook-messenger/), [Telegram](https://ooni.org/nettest/telegram/), and [Signal](https://ooni.org/nettest/signal) are blocked.\n\nYour results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.io/world/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).
Test the blocking of censorship circumvention tools

Check whether [Psiphon](https://ooni.io/nettest/psiphon/), [Tor](https://ooni.io/nettest/tor/) or [RiseupVPN](https://ooni.io/nettest/riseupvpn/) are blocked.\n\nYour results will be published on [OONI Explorer](https://explorer.ooni.org/) and [OONI API](https://api.ooni.io/).

The Open Observatory of Network Interference (OONI) is a free software project under The Tor Project that aims to increase transparency of internet censorship around the world.\n\nSince 2012, OONI\'s global community has been measuring networks in more than 200 countries. Some of these measurements serve as evidence of internet censorship.
By enabling automatic testing, OONI Probe tests will run automatically multiple times per day. Your test results will automatically get published on OONI Explorer: https://explorer.ooni.org/
This information (e.g. IT for Italy) is required to identify which country the measurements are collected from. Are you sure you want to disable this option?

By publishing results, you are increasing transparency of network interference and supporting the OONI community. \n\nNetwork information (i.e. Autonomous System Number) is required for identifying Internet Service Providers.
